# Docs authority

- Start with `AGENTS.md` and `USER_STORY.md`: Priya's journey is the north star.
- Visual and interaction contract: `docs/01_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`.
- Engineering rules, stack, milestones, and cut line: `BUILD.md`.
- Remaining work / goal+loop prompts: `PLAN.md` (consolidated). `docs/02_*` is an archive stub.
- Screen/design prompt details: `docs/03_CLAUDE_DESIGN_BRIEF.md`.
- Vision, scope, demo script, and compliance: `docs/04_CLAUDE_PROJECT.md`.
- Genericness definitions and detector methodology: `docs/05_GENERICNESS_METHODOLOGY.md`.
- Illustration-first educational / interactive visualization plan: `docs/07_VISUALIZATION_PLAN.md` (separate from `PLAN.md` checklists). Do not name external authors, sites, or projects when describing this style.
- AI design methods + style-addition playbook: `docs/08_AI_DESIGN_METHODS.md` (packaged judgment / build by piece / reference board). Principle-only — no third-party author, site, skill-marketplace, or tool names.
- If `BUILD.md` and archived `docs/02_*` drift, treat root `BUILD.md` as the working source.
- Do not read `.env` or `.env.local` for routine work; use `.env.example` and README docs for configuration.
